<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[94,719,346,691]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[94,341,346,371]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Description: Length:</emphasis>
<quantity box="[353,485,346,371]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.05" metricValueMax="6.4" metricValueMin="5.7" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" unit="mm" value="6.05" valueMax="6.4" valueMin="5.7">5.7-6.4 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[500,648,346,371]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Colouration:</emphasis>
Head black, frons and clypeus dark brown; antennae dark brown, antennomeres I-III testaceous ventrally, antennomeres IX-XI light brown; labium and maxillae light brown, labial and maxillary palpi testaceous to light brown; pronotum entirely pale yellow; elytra greyish brown, with a yellowish to light-brown apical patch; wings dark brown; legs pale yellow with dark-brown spots on the apex of femora dorsally, dorsal surface of tibiae and distal tarsomeres; thorax and abdominal tergites dark brown, abdominal ventrites light brown (
<figureCitation box="[436,498,666,691]" captionStart="Figures 1-6" captionStartId="3.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[152,1356,206,2041]" captionTargetId="figure-1@3.[151,1360,204,2044]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figures 1-6:Dorsal habitus ofMacromalthinus species.(1) M.guyanensis sp.nov.(2)M.luteoapicalissp.nov.(3)M.orapuensis sp.nov.(4) M.piceiventrissp.nov. (5) M.quadratithorax sp.nov.(6)M.xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384149/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[94,719,730,1875]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[94,171,730,755]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Males:</emphasis>
Head large, 1.3 times wider than the pronotum, temples elongate, strongly tapering posteriorly, vertex concave. Eyes large, oblong, very prominent. Antennae filiform, slender, covered with thin short setae; antennomere I elongate, II very short, 0.4 the length of I, III twice longer than II, IV-XI nearly same length as I. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[101,173,922,947]" captionStart="Figures 7-12" captionStartId="4.[869,937,1217,1242]" captionTargetBox="[869,1493,204,1187]" captionTargetId="figure-697@4.[869,1493,204,1187]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figures 7-12: Pronotum of Macromalthinus species. (7) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (8) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov. (9) M. orapuensis sp. nov. (10) M. piceiventris sp. nov. (11) M. quadratithorax sp. nov. (12) M. xerophilus sp. nov. Scale bars:1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384151" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384151/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) subquadrate, 1.1 times wider than long; anterior margin slightly arched, lateral margins almost parallel, slightly constricted near anterior angles; pronotal surface elevated antero-medially and near posterior angles, forming a V-shaped shallow groove posteriorly. Elytra short, rugulose, densely covered with short and thin setae; sutures broadly dehiscent from posterior half; apex swollen dorsally. Legs slender; fore femur (
<figureCitation box="[562,637,1146,1171]" captionStart="Figures 13-18" captionStartId="5.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[97,1416,991,2040]" captionTargetId="figure-354@5.[94,1417,986,2044]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figures 13-18: Fore femur of Macromalthinus species. (13) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (14) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov.(15) M. orapuensis sp.nov.(16) M. piceiventris sp.nov.(17) M. quadratithoraxsp.nov.(18) M. xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384153" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384153/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) slightly swollen,with weak,rounded ventral tooth; femora,tibiae and tarsomeres increasing in length from fore to hind legs. Tarsal claws simple, not toothed. Abdominal tergites and sternites sclerotized; ventrites densely covered with long thin setae; glandular pores not prominent; distal margin of ventrite VI arched and slightly sclerotized; ventrite VII (
<figureCitation box="[233,311,1370,1395]" captionStart="Figures 19-24" captionStartId="6.[170,238,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[172,1491,1272,2042]" captionTargetId="figure-506@6.[170,1493,1269,2044]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figures 19-24:Ventrite VII of males of Macromalthinus species.(19) M.guyanensis sp.nov.(20) M.luteoapicalis sp.nov.(21)M. orapuensis sp.nov.(22) M.piceiventris sp.nov.(23) M.quadratithorax sp.nov.(24) M.xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384156/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
) H-shaped, lateral margins sinuous, broader anteriorly, with broad membranous area anteriorly and deep posterior notch; ventrite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[567,641,1434,1459]" captionStart="Figures 25-30" captionStartId="7.[794,862,2010,2035]" captionTargetBox="[798,1414,205,1979]" captionTargetId="figure-491@7.[794,1418,204,1980]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figures 25-30: Ventrite VIII of males of Macromalthinus species. (25) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (26) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov. (27) M. orapuensis sp.nov.(28)M.piceiventrissp.nov.(29) M.quadratithoraxsp.nov.(30) M.xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384158" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384158/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
) asymmetrical, oblong, strongly convex, without ridges; distal margin notched at left side, tip acute. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[638,712,1498,1523]" captionStart="Figures 31-36" captionStartId="8.[170,238,2042,2067]" captionTargetBox="[171,1491,674,2008]" captionTargetId="figure-183@8.[170,1493,670,2012]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 31-36: Aedeagus of Macromalthinus species. (31) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (32) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov. (33) M. orapuensis sp. nov. (34) M. piceiventris sp.nov.(35) M. quadratithorax sp.nov.(36) M. xerophilus sp.nov. Abbreviations:pt = prolongation of tegmen, sp = setiferous prolongation,rp = right paramere, lp = left paramere,ml = median lobe.Scale bars:0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384160" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384160/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
) with right prolongation of tegmen short, projected dorsally, without apophysis on its dorsal surface; left setiferous prolongation short, wide, bearing thick, short apical setae; right paramere elongate, slightly curved, with slight constriction near apex; left paramere elongate, narrow, flat, apex rounded; median lobe straight, broad, apex membranous. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[313,639,1722,1747]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Measurements of 
<typeStatus box="[524,635,1722,1747]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">holotype</typeStatus>
:
</emphasis>
TL: 6.0; AL: 4.8; OL: 0.51; HW: 1.12; IOW: 0.57; IAW: 0.2; PL: 0.86; PW: 0.93; EL: 1.8; EW: 1.24. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Length of each antennomere:</emphasis>
aI: 0.37; aII: 0.18; aIII: 0.30; aIV: 0.43; aV: 0.45; aVI: 0.47; aVII: 0.47; aVIII: 0.48; aIX: 0.48; aX: 0.43; aXI: 0.46.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[94,719,1914,2131]" lastBlockId="13.[794,1418,218,467]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[94,187,1914,1939]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Female:</emphasis>
similar to male; eyes smaller, less prominent; fore femora slender, without intumescence or tooth; ventrite VI entire, not notched posteriorly; ventrite VII (
<figureCitation box="[101,175,2010,2035]" captionStart="Figures 37-42" captionStartId="9.[94,162,2074,2099]" captionTargetBox="[94,1414,1424,2040]" captionTargetId="figure-592@9.[94,1417,1420,2044]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figures 37-42:VentriteVII offemales ofMacromalthinusspecies.(37) M.guyanensis sp.nov.(38)M.luteoapicalissp.nov.(39) M.orapuensissp.nov.(40)M.piceiventris sp.nov.(41) M. quadratithoraxsp.nov.(42) M. xerophilus sp.nov.Scale bars:0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384162" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384162/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 41</figureCitation>
) short, wide, lateral margins arched, slightly narrowed near angles, posterior margin slightly projected, strongly sinuous, forming two rounded lobes; base of coxites (
<figureCitation box="[186,262,2106,2131]" captionStart="Figures 43-48" captionStartId="10.[869,937,2010,2035]" captionTargetBox="[873,1490,1055,1976]" captionTargetId="figure-666@10.[869,1493,1054,1980]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Figures 43-48: Coxites of Macromalthinus species. (43) M. guyanensis sp. nov. (44) M. luteoapicalis sp. nov. (45) M. orapuensis sp. nov. (46) M. piceiventris sp. nov. (47) M. quadratithorax sp. nov. (48) M. xerophilus sp. nov. Scale bars:0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5384164" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5384164/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Fig. 47</figureCitation>
) elongate, slender, apex very short, with short and broad projection behind styles bearing few thin setae; styles short, slightly wider apically, bearing thick setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
Measurements of medium size female 
<typeStatus box="[794,905,314,339]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">paratype</typeStatus>
:
</emphasis>
TL: 5.6; AL: 5.12; OL: 0.55; HW: 1.15; IOW: 0.58; IAW: 0.21; PL: 0.87; PW: 0.97; EL: 1.70; EW: 1.22. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Length of each antennomere:</emphasis>
aI: 0.46; aII: 0.12; aIII: 0.38; aIV: 0.51; aV: 0.53; aVI: 0.53; aVII: 0.53; aVIII: 0.55; aIX: 0.52; aX: 0.47; aXI: 0.47.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[794,1417,506,595]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[794,929,506,531]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derivative of the Latin words 
<emphasis box="[868,978,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">quadratus</emphasis>
(square) + 
<emphasis box="[1104,1174,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">thorax</emphasis>
(pronotum), referring to the shape of the pronotum in this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
